                        <gml:description>HRV1 and HRV2 instruments on-board the SPOT-1, SPOT-2 and SPOT-3 satellites
            are high resolution imaging spectrometer operating in the visible and near-infrared spectrum. Data
            are acquired through three multi-spectral bands (XS1, XS2, and XS3) with a 20 metres spatial resolution
            and one panchromatic band (PAN) at 10 metres spatial resolution. These two instruments may be
            independently depointed across-track to get a viewing angle in the range [-27,+27] degrees.</gml:description>
			
